Steps (say like practical)
Login to AWS Console
Go to IAM (Identity and Access Management)
Click Users → Add User
Enter username (e.g., student1)
Select Programmatic access / Console access
Click Next → Set Permissions
Choose:
Attach policy (like AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess)
Click Create UserAssign Role (RBAC)
Go to Roles → Create Role
Select service (EC2 / User)
Attach permission policies
Assign role to userGo to IAM → Users
Select user
Click Security Credentials
Enable MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)
Scan QR using authenticator 
appData at Rest (Storage Encryption)
Go to S3 (Storage)
Create bucket
Enable:
“Default Encryption”
Choose AES-256 or KMS
Use HTTPS instead of HTTP
Configure SSL/TLS certificate
Ensure secure API communication
Open KMS (Key Management Service)
Create key
Assign permissions
Use key in S3 / database encryption

======================================================================================
Enable Monitoring
Go to CloudWatch
Enable metrics for EC2 / S3
Go to CloudTrail
Click Create Trail
Enable:
Log all API activity
Store logs in S3
Go to CloudWatch → Alarms
Click Create Alarm
Select metric:
CPU usage / login attempts
Set threshold (e.g., >80%)
Configure notification (email)
Check:
Failed login attempts
Unusual API calls
Block suspicious IP
Disable compromised user
Modify permissions
Unknown IP access
